on a regular basis.</i>

03:11.476 --> 03:14.270
<i>This is the telephone booth
at 53rd and 8th...</i>

03:14.477 --> 03:18.690
<i>... perhaps the last vestige of privacy
on Manhattan 's West Side.</i>

03:18.898 --> 03:22.194
<i>It is the last booth of its type,
still in regular operation.</i>

03:22.402 --> 03:25.197
<i>Up to 300 calls daily originate here.</i>

03:25.405 --> 03:29.824
<i>This location has been burglarized
41 times in the last six months.</i>

03:30.034 --> 03:32.662
<i>Verizon has scheduled this structure
to be torn down...</i>

03:32.871 --> 03:36.582
<i>... and replaced with a kiosk
as of 8 a.m. tomorrow.</i>

03:36.791 --> 03:38.667
<i>Hardly two blocks away...</i>

03:38.876 --> 03:42.922
<i>... meet the man who is to be
the final occupant of that booth.</i>

03:43.131 --> 03:45.467
Donny. Donny. Donny, listen to me.

03:45.674 --> 03:49.259
I said I'd get you magazine coverage,
and I'm getting you in a magazine.

03:49.469 --> 03:52.473
Look, you gotta trust me.
No means yes to these people.

03:52.681 --> 03:54.515
Get "What's Up?" magazine
on the line.

03:54.724 --> 03:55.808
Yeah, I heard you.

03:56.017 --> 03:58.102
Donny, I got "What's Up?" magazine
on the line.

03:58.311 --> 04:00.562
They wanna know about you,
so I'm hanging up.

04:00.980 --> 04:03.608
This is Erica or Lars.
I can't tell the difference.

04:03.816 --> 04:05.527
- You got Stu.
- We said no.

04:05.735 --> 04:08.196
I didn't hear you,
so I'm giving you a second chance.

04:08.405 --> 04:10.029
- We don't do magicians.
- Magicians?

04:10.239 --> 04:13.657
Donny G is an artist who happens
to look like a supermodel.

04:13.867 --> 04:16.870
"- The New Guys" is offering him the cover.
"- New Guys" wants him?

04:17.079 --> 04:19.539
And I haven't told my client,
my favorite client...

04:19.748 --> 04:23.042
...that I am making this call, all right?
He wants "New Guys."

04:23.209 --> 04:25.295
I want you and I can make him
come around...

04:25.463 --> 04:28.591
...but you'll lose us if I don't
hear from you by end of business.

04:28.840 --> 04:31.342
Get "New Guys". Tell him "What's Up?"
Is offering a cover.

04:31.509 --> 04:32.968
Okay. Big Q.

04:33.219 --> 04:37.306
Adam, I know three people looking
for dog walkers. That could be you.

04:37.557 --> 04:40.852
"Sit. Stay. Don't worry, Fluffy,
I'll clean your shit and wipe your ass. "

04:41.101 --> 04:43.146
- You got Stu.
- What's up with my party, Stu?

04:43.353 --> 04:46.147
I was just telling my assistant
to get my favorite client...

04:46.315 --> 04:48.568
...on the phone,
and here you are. Nice.

04:51.027 --> 04:54.279
Listen. Seriously, we gotta look
at a new night for your release party.

04:54.488 --> 04:57.702
There are two premieres, a fundraiser.
All the happening places are booked.

04:57.909 --> 04:58.951
If we move the date...

04:59.160 --> 05:02.497
Voodoo on you-do, motherfucker,
from Big Q to Big Stu!

05:02.706 --> 05:04.916
- Big Q, be reasonable.
- Motherfucker, I'm a gangster!

05:05.123 --> 05:08.711
- I don't gotta be reasonable!
- You're cutting out.

05:08.920 --> 05:12.841
Next time I'm gonna kill your cracker-ass
if you keep talking about me like that!

05:13.049 --> 05:14.340
Right?

05:14.591 --> 05:17.886
N.Y.P.D. Blue, 11 o'clock.

05:18.260 --> 05:21.514
Stuey, the hardest working
PR guy. How's business?

05:21.724 --> 05:24.184
How many times I have
to tell you, Wyatt? I'm a publicist.

05:24.393 --> 05:25.935
- Tickets.
- Tickets.

05:26.143 --> 05:28.145
Four for Britney Spears, right?

05:28.354 --> 05:30.357
You put the "Ho"
in show business, Stuey.

05:30.565 --> 05:33.525
It's Stu. What do you got for me?

05:33.736 --> 05:38.697
They just checked Mrs. Sharp
into Bellevue again.

05:38.905 --> 05:41.409
- Page Six. Tell Britney I send my love.
- All right.

05:41.618 --> 05:43.284
Enjoy the show.

05:43.995 --> 05:47.331
Hold on a sec. Page Six, this is Lana.

05:47.538 --> 05:50.876
Bless you. Lana, it's Stu Shepard.
Bless you.

05:51.085 --> 05:52.878
- Is it you or your boss calling?
- It's me.

05:53.088 --> 05:55.171
I'm looking for some
mutual back-scratching.

05:55.379 --> 05:59.092
You get my privileged N.Y.P.D. Blue
info and I get you to save my ass.

05:59.299 --> 06:00.968
Not now, Stu. I'm a sick woman.

06:01.177 --> 06:03.055
This is going
to make you feel better.

06:03.262 --> 06:07.057
Tony-winning producer Jeffrey Sharp
tossed his wife back into drug rehab.

06:07.265 --> 06:09.433
Nice. What do you want
for that little tidbit?

06:09.642 --> 06:12.938
You better be nice to me while I'm on
the way up and taking your calls.

06:13.147 --> 06:16.483
The higher the monkey climbs,
the more you see of his ass.

06:16.692 --> 06:17.943
Have a heart, Lana.

06:18.152 --> 06:21.946
Listen, today my half-wit assistant
faxed you regarding my favorite client.

06:22.155 --> 06:24.282
Great singer,
about to turn great actress.

06:24.489 --> 06:27.785
- Another little Miss Tits and Ass?
- Look, I'm on cell, no names.

06:27.994 --> 06:31.289
That was strictly in-office information.
You didn't print it, did you?

06:31.496 --> 06:34.124
- I got it.
- All right, tell me Richard didn't see it.

06:34.332 --> 06:36.169
He didn't put it in the column?

06:36.376 --> 06:38.587
Stu's on the phone,
scared he's gonna lose his job.

06:38.796 --> 06:41.130
His office sent you something
by mistake. He wants it.

06:41.339 --> 06:44.467
You tell him T.F.B.
Put that at the top of the column.

06:44.676 --> 06:46.469
- Stu, it ran, sorry.
- Yeah?

06:46.678 --> 06:48.930
- Oh, God. Oh, no.
- I'm really sorry.

06:49.139 --> 06:50.890
Yes!

06:51.766 --> 06:55.144
"What's Up?" magazine offered Donny G
a photo in "What's Hot and Happening."

06:55.353 --> 06:58.065
- Fuck them. Make them sweat.
- He's on a conference call.

06:58.231 --> 07:01.693
He could take a while. Yeah, can he call
you back? Okay. All right, bye.

07:01.901 --> 07:03.152
- Pretty smooth.
- Thank you.

07:03.360 --> 07:05.446
If you can absorb
everything I teach you...

07:05.611 --> 07:09.074
...focus and get a new wardrobe,
you can make it big in public relations.

07:09.241 --> 07:10.827
- I got a sense.
- Cool. Cool. Cool.

07:11.035 --> 07:12.202
- Up, T?
- How you doing, man?

07:12.411 --> 07:14.205
Mario's!

07:15.745 --> 07:17.831
Hey! Hey! Hey! Not so fast, Stu!

07:18.083 --> 07:21.378
How come you run every time
you go past my place, huh?

07:21.587 --> 07:23.672
- Because I'm busy, Mario.
- Yeah?

07:23.881 --> 07:26.132
Well, no more drinks or free meals, okay?

07:26.341 --> 07:30.052
One lousy mention in the "Post",
you expect to eat for six months? No!

07:30.512 --> 07:33.598
Mario, maybe I could throw
the hippest party this month your way.

07:33.806 --> 07:36.349
- Stu.
- No, I couldn't. My clients would kill me.

07:36.600 --> 07:40.229
- What hip party?
- It's just Big Q, the hottest new rap star.

07:40.437 --> 07:43.191
- There'll be local TV coverage...
- Nine and 11.

07:43.399 --> 07:45.610
MTV, BET, VH1.

07:45.817 --> 07:48.486
But I promised other clients,
people who actually pay me.

07:48.695 --> 07:51.071
- No, you owe me.
- It's gotta be the night of the 18th.

07:51.280 --> 07:54.284
Toss in a buffet for 80 people,
record company will pick up the booze...

07:54.493 --> 07:56.160
...and I will deliver you celebrities.

07:56.745 --> 07:59.245
Anything you want, okay?

07:59.455 --> 08:02.667
Expand the menu, wallpaper
those bathrooms, for God's sake.

08:02.917 --> 08:04.711
You only get one shot
with celebrities.

08:05.211 --> 08:07.339
Thank you. Thank you, Stu!

08:07.547 --> 08:09.214
- That was fucking brilliant.
- Listen.

08:09.465 --> 08:12.633
Call Big Q. Tell him we got him
the hippest place in town on his date.

08:12.842 --> 08:14.011
- Call "What's Up?"
- Yeah.

08:14.219 --> 08:15.470
We'll take their offer.

08:15.679 --> 08:17.973
Messenger a bottle of Jameson's
to Lana at Page Six...

08:18.180 --> 08:20.474
...with a note saying... Write this down.
- Got it.

08:20.684 --> 08:24.396
- Irish chicken soup. Love, Stu.
- "Irish chicken soup. Love, Stu. "

08:24.605 --> 08:26.523
- All right, no harm being gracious.
- Yeah.

08:26.732 --> 08:29.067
Okay. Actually, better off,
deliver it over yourself.

08:29.275 --> 08:31.276
- Get to know the players.
- I'll do that.

08:31.485 --> 08:32.777
Thank you for teaching me.

08:32.986 --> 08:35.783
- And, Adam, don't you have a suit?
- Actually, no.

08:36.032 --> 08:37.909
Here. Get yourself one.

08:38.116 --> 08:41.035
- I'm gonna start paying you soon.
- Yeah, I hope so.

08:41.244 --> 08:44.163
- You got a bunch of messages.
- I'm late for a meeting. Hold them.

08:44.414 --> 08:45.457
- All right.
- All right.

08:45.666 --> 08:49.127
- See you, Stu!
- See you, Adam!

09:18.404 --> 09:20.448
- Excuse me.
- I'm trying to make a call here.

09:20.656 --> 09:23.867
This is for you. Half-pepperoni,
half-mushroom, extra crisp.

09:24.076 --> 09:26.578
You ever heard of delivering
a pizza to a phone booth?

09:26.745 --> 09:28.122
I don't think so.

09:28.330 --> 09:32.294
Gentleman occupying phone booth,
53rd, between Broadway and 8th.

09:32.501 --> 09:34.794
It's a mistake.

09:35.254 --> 09:38.046
What am I supposed to do
with the pie? It's all paid for.

09:38.297 --> 09:40.216
There's a homeless guy
around the block.

09:40.425 --> 09:44.138
Give him the pizza and say "You can turn
away, but you can't make it go away. "

09:44.347 --> 09:47.307
He'll think I'm trying to poison him.
They always get that idea.

09:47.474 --> 09:49.934
Get off the fucking pizza, all right?

09:51.186 --> 09:53.438
That language is uncalled for.

09:53.647 --> 09:55.522
Holy shit!

09:55.731 --> 09:59.150
I'm sorry. Please return to sender.

09:59.360 --> 10:01.445
Fuck off.

10:02.363 --> 10:06.867
Here you go, $5. Eat the pizza yourself.
You look like you could use a good meal.

10:26.260 --> 10:27.260
Hello.

10:27.512 --> 10:31.806
Pam, could you believe some nut case
just tried to deliver me a pizza?

10:32.015 --> 10:36.020
Why are you always in the same
phone booth, same time, every day?

10:36.228 --> 10:40.231
- Well, it's quitting time, right?
- Thank God, we were mobbed today.

10:40.439 --> 10:41.607
So how's your day?

10:41.815 --> 10:44.693
It's getting better
by the minute, sweetheart.

10:44.902 --> 10:47.155
Who's the most famous person
you publicized today?

10:47.364 --> 10:49.449
- You.
- Really?

10:49.658 --> 10:53.034
I told a few columnists Mel Gibson
was looking for actresses for his film.

10:53.285 --> 10:57.040
And I said the possibilities
were Cameron Diaz, Julia Roberts...

10:57.249 --> 10:59.834
...and my favorite client, you.

11:00.042 --> 11:01.168
You didn't really do that.

11:01.377 --> 11:03.586
First step toward being noticed
is being mentioned.

11:03.797 --> 11:05.921
I just got out of a
conference at the City Hotel.

11:06.087 --> 11:07.717
I was thinking you
could come down.

11:07.966 --> 11:11.845
There are a couple of people and a few
martinis I'd like to introduce you to.

11:12.053 --> 11:13.931
- Stu, I...
- Listen, Pam. Pam. Pam.

11:14.138 --> 11:16.432
It's about time we talked
about your career. Come on.

11:16.641 --> 11:22.063
I feel awful but I promised my scene
partner that I would rehearse for class.

11:22.271 --> 11:25.566
We're doing a scene from "Jerry Maguire."
I'm playing Renée Zellweger's part.

11:25.732 --> 11:28.444
That's great. Look, I rescheduled
a meeting to see you...

11:28.652 --> 11:30.530
...but I guess I can reschedule it back.

11:30.739 --> 11:33.115
- Are you mad?
- Don't worry about it. I'm not mad.

11:33.281 --> 11:34.866
Maybe tomorrow.

11:35.075 --> 11:36.410
Yeah, later.

11:36.659 --> 11:38.161
- Look, Stu...
- What?

11:38.370 --> 11:39.955
Big kiss.

11:40.164 --> 11:41.623
You too.

11:52.634 --> 11:54.718
<i>- Yeah.
- Isn't it funny?</i>

11:54.928 --> 11:57.387
<i>You hear a phone ring,
and it could be anybody...</i>

11:57.596 --> 12:00.182
<i>... but a ringing phone has to be
answered, doesn't it?</i>

12:00.390 --> 12:01.433
What?

12:01.641 --> 12:04.186
<i>I hope you realize
how you've hurt my feelings.</i>

12:04.393 --> 12:07.897
<i>- Who the fuck is this?
- Don't think about leaving that phone.</i>

12:08.105 --> 12:10.649
<i>- Wrong number, pal.
- It was a perfectly delicious pizza.</i>

12:10.858 --> 12:13.028
<i>You're certainly going
to wish you had accepted it.</i>

12:13.236 --> 12:16.530
Naturally, this is part of the gag.
The pizza bit. That was funny shit.

12:16.740 --> 12:19.910
<i>Well, its purpose was to keep
your strength up for what's coming next.</i>

12:20.159 --> 12:23.245
<i>- What's coming next is I'm hanging up.
- Oh, no, you won't.</i>

12:23.453 --> 12:26.333
<i>- You're going to learn to obey me.
- Obey you?</i>

12:26.541 --> 12:29.083
<i>- Who is this?
- Someone who enjoys watching you.</i>

12:29.293 --> 12:30.335
Watching me?

12:30.542 --> 12:34.672
<i>Yes, I love the suit you're wearing today.
Black on raspberry sorbet. Very Italian.</i>

12:35.840 --> 12:37.758
Where...? Where are you?

12:37.967 --> 12:42.137
<i>There are hundreds of windows out there.
Why don't you check them out?</i>

12:46.768 --> 12:49.645
<i>- So, what am I doing now?
- You're scratching your head.</i>

12:49.853 --> 12:53.357
<i>Now you're brushing your hair back.</i>

12:54.441 --> 12:57.360
<i>That's not very nice, Stu.</i>

12:58.237 --> 12:59.613
Did you call me Stu?

13:00.655 --> 13:04.284
<i>- Who's Stu? I don't know any Stu.
- Why, do you prefer Stuart?</i>

13:04.493 --> 13:06.578
A lot of people in this
neighborhood know me.

13:06.744 --> 13:10.415
<i>Stuart Shepard, 1326 West
51st Street, Third Floor, front.</i>

13:10.624 --> 13:13.666
<i>- Go mind-fuck some other guy, pal.
- I know Pamela McFadden too.</i>

13:13.875 --> 13:16.753
<i>It's not in your best interest
to disconnect me.</i>

13:17.003 --> 13:19.298
<i>Someone could get hurt.</i>

13:19.507 --> 13:22.302
<i>What's the matter, Stu?</i>

13:22.510 --> 13:25.221
If you're some fucked-up,
failed actor I wouldn't handle...

13:25.387 --> 13:28.932
...or some prick intern I fired, I will
hunt you down and I will crush you.

13:29.141 --> 13:30.976
You will never work in this town.

13:31.184 --> 13:32.604
I can turn people into gods...

13:32.811 --> 13:36.313
...and I can turn you into a total
fucking loser if you weren't one already.

13:36.564 --> 13:39.777
Do you hear me?
Am I upsetting you? Hello.

13:39.984 --> 13:42.986
Oh, you think I'm gonna, what?
Pay you off or something?

13:43.196 --> 13:45.948
<i>- Tell me what you want.
- Now you want to talk to me.</i>

13:46.156 --> 13:48.241
Did Adam at my office
put you up to this?

13:48.450 --> 13:51.120
<i>No, I thought this up all by myself.</i>

13:51.330 --> 13:52.831
Keep thinking. I'm hanging up.

13:53.038 --> 13:57.542
<i>I'll say hi to your wife, Kelly, for you.
Talk to you later.</i>

13:58.041 --> 14:00.126
What the...?

14:02.256 --> 14:05.466
<i>The callback feature
cannot be activated...</i>

14:05.884 --> 14:07.552
Motherfucker.

14:34.788 --> 14:39.497
<i>- Tell me what you want.
- I want your complete attention.</i>

14:40.749 --> 14:44.545
<i>- Are you an actor?
- Yes. One of your pathetic failed ones.</i>

14:44.796 --> 14:47.173
<i>- It's tough when you're not known.
- Tell me about it.</i>

14:47.381 --> 14:51.510
<i>You don't have to hunt me and crush me.
I can't get work in this town as it is.</i>

14:51.718 --> 14:55.097
<i>I've done some off-Broadway, some
off-Manhattan plays, but that dried up.</i>

14:55.305 --> 14:58.184
<i>Now I wait tables, clean toilets,
anything to make the rent.</i>

14:58.391 --> 15:00.144
<i>I'm a walking cliché.</i>

15:00.351 --> 15:02.270
I can help you.
I can get you auditions.

15:02.477 --> 15:04.688
<i>Auditions? You're not an agent.
You're a publicist.</i>

15:04.898 --> 15:08.151
Yeah, but I have contacts.
I know agents. I can get you an audition.

15:08.358 --> 15:10.360
<i>- Really?
- Yeah.</i>

15:10.570 --> 15:13.613
<i>Well, there is someone
I'd like you to call.</i>

15:13.823 --> 15:14.907
Name it.

15:15.116 --> 15:19.162
<i>Try the number you dialed
when you first got into the booth.</i>

15:20.038 --> 15:21.956
<i>- I don't know what you're talking about.
- No?</i>

15:22.165 --> 15:24.124
<i>Lucky you then,
because I wrote it down.</i>

15:24.333 --> 15:27.752
<i>I can see every number you pressed.
Let's see if Pam is still at work.</i>

15:28.002 --> 15:30.088
<i>- No.
- Then I guess I'll have to do it.</i>

15:30.297 --> 15:33.301
<i>- Look, don't!
- Too late. It's already ringing.</i>

15:33.508 --> 15:37.761
<i>- I'll put her on speaker so you can hear.
- You're fucking kidding me.</i>

15:37.971 --> 15:41.724
<i>Stu, I never kid.</i>

15:46.978 --> 15:50.442
<i>- Hello.
- Well, hello, Pam.</i>

15:50.650 --> 15:53.776
<i>- Hi, who's this?
- It's a good friend of Stu's.</i>

15:53.985 --> 15:56.904
<i>- And he hasn't got many.
- You know Stu?</i>

15:57.113 --> 16:00.117
<i>I know he lies.</i>

16:00.325 --> 16:02.286
<i>- Who is this?
- Don't worry about that.</i>

16:02.495 --> 16:06.039
<i>Stu's listening in. He can hear
what we're saying about him.</i>

16:06.248 --> 16:09.501
- Stu, is that true? Are you there?
- Pam, hang up the goddamn phone!

16:09.708 --> 16:11.751
<i>She can't hear you, Stu.</i>

16:11.961 --> 16:16.089
<i>Pam, I'm afraid Stu hasn't been
totally honest with you.</i>

16:16.298 --> 16:17.883
- What do you mean?
- Don't do this.

16:18.050 --> 16:20.551
<i>- Stu has been lying to you.
- Pam, hang up.</i>

16:20.760 --> 16:22.930
<i>Now, why would a man
who has a cell phone...</i>

16:23.139 --> 16:26.393
<i>... call you every day
from a phone booth?</i>

16:26.602 --> 16:31.562
<i>- Because he said it's quiet.
- Pam, that's just stupid.</i>

16:31.771 --> 16:34.358
<i>It's because his wife checks
his cell phone bills.</i>

16:34.566 --> 16:39.655
<i>- No record of his calls to you.
- Jesus Christ.</i>

16:39.862 --> 16:43.742
<i>- He said he wasn't married.
- Oh, he's married.</i>

16:43.949 --> 16:47.662
<i>Her name is Kelly. I've never seen her
but she sounds lovely.</i>

16:47.869 --> 16:50.538
<i>Why do you think
he invites you to the City Hotel?</i>

16:50.748 --> 16:52.665
<i>- Cheap rooms for cheap girls.
- Asshole.</i>

16:52.874 --> 16:55.753
<i>He's telling you all this
so you'll sleep with him.</i>

16:55.961 --> 16:58.504
- He's lying, Pam. Don't listen.
- I know that, okay?

16:58.672 --> 17:01.049
I may be from Montana,
but we have men there also.

17:01.257 --> 17:03.551
I wasn't planning
