- I'm flattered.
- Operator 553. What is your emergency?

30:36.817 --> 30:37.984
Will you please respond?

30:38.151 --> 30:41.488
What was so interesting about a guy
in a phone booth on 53rd and 8th?

30:41.654 --> 30:43.615
The Stu Show. "Better than TV."

30:43.866 --> 30:47.161
Look, how'd I get so lucky to be
picked up by a killer with a rifle?!

30:47.368 --> 30:51.622
<i>You had it made.
Kelly at home, Pam on the side.</i>

30:51.831 --> 30:55.711
<i>I saw Pam once. I followed her
to her restaurant. Lovely.</i>

30:55.920 --> 30:58.295
<i>Life has given you
more than your fair share, Stu.</i>

30:58.504 --> 31:00.839
<i>But it appears you don't appreciate it.</i>

31:01.049 --> 31:03.842
Look, look, listen,
appearances can be deceiving.

31:04.051 --> 31:07.763
I may look confident, but I'm really,
actually just crying out for help!

31:07.971 --> 31:09.306
Help! You know?

31:09.515 --> 31:14.688
<i>I'm trying to help you, Stu,
but you won't help yourself.</i>

31:18.023 --> 31:20.776
<i>- Fuck.
- What's the matter, Stu?</i>

31:23.694 --> 31:26.156
<i>- You shot me!
- It's time you learn, Stu.</i>

31:26.365 --> 31:29.909
<i>- Deception can't go unrewarded.
- Deception! What fucking deception?</i>

31:30.118 --> 31:35.706
<i>"Are you in need of immediate police
or medical response?"</i>

31:36.458 --> 31:39.544
Shit. You bugged the fucking booth.

31:39.753 --> 31:42.128
That's how you knew.
That's how you knew about Pam.

31:42.337 --> 31:46.299
<i>- You picked the wrong person to lie to.
- Look, I didn't pick you.</i>

31:46.507 --> 31:49.094
It must have been
your flashy suit that attracted me.

31:49.302 --> 31:52.096
I get fucked on account of my clothes?
That why you killed Leon?

31:52.306 --> 31:54.182
<i>I didn't kill Leon because
of the way he dressed.</i>

31:54.391 --> 31:57.100
And those other two guys as well?
Did they dress too nice?

31:57.309 --> 32:00.438
<i>You must feel really expensive
when you walk out the door.</i>

32:00.857 --> 32:02.107
All right, here come the cops.

32:02.315 --> 32:03.816
What are you gonna do? Run?

32:04.024 --> 32:06.151
<i>No, I'm not a coward
like some people I know.</i>

32:06.402 --> 32:09.112
<i>- You can get away if you run now.
- You'll blame me for Leon.</i>

32:09.321 --> 32:12.323
No, no, I'll confess I shot him
with my fucking phone.

32:12.574 --> 32:15.037
<i>Well, then I urge you
to keep one thing in mind, Stu.</i>

32:15.244 --> 32:18.496
<i>Take a look at your chest. You saw how
accurate I can be, how lethal.</i>

32:18.746 --> 32:20.583
Kill me now,
and you give yourself away.

32:20.792 --> 32:23.126
<i>Not with a silencer.
It would take these guys...</i>

32:23.335 --> 32:26.587
<i>... the rest of the day to figure out it
wasn't one of their own men that did it.</i>

32:26.796 --> 32:29.256
<i>You can be shot 41 times
for pulling out your wallet.</i>

32:29.505 --> 32:33.302
Throw down your weapon
and come out with your hands raised.

32:33.552 --> 32:35.512
<i>- Ignore him.
- Yeah, what if they open fire?</i>

32:35.721 --> 32:38.390
<i>They won't. Look around you, Stu.</i>

32:38.640 --> 32:40.892
<i>Do you see the tourists
with the video cameras?</i>

32:41.101 --> 32:42.853
<i>The ones hoping the cops
will blow you away...</i>

32:43.062 --> 32:45.856
<i>... so they can sell the tape
"to" The Most Gory Police Shootouts?</i>

32:46.065 --> 32:48.691
<i>Don't worry, they'll keep
the police on their best behavior.</i>

32:48.899 --> 32:53.989
<i>So long as you don't take
hostile action, you should be safe.</i>

32:54.198 --> 32:55.698
Safe? You call this safe?

32:55.906 --> 33:00.160
I got a whole fucking precinct here
with guns pointed my way.

33:00.870 --> 33:06.000
With both hands raised,
moving slowly, step out of the booth.

33:06.209 --> 33:08.961
If we see any signs of a weapon
we will respond.

33:09.211 --> 33:10.836
You won't because there isn't any!

33:11.046 --> 33:12.964
Put down the phone
and raise your hands!

33:13.214 --> 33:15.258
Look, I can't.
I'm on an important call.

33:15.802 --> 33:17.385
Verify this information for me.

33:17.593 --> 33:19.888
The guy in the booth
shot that guy over there...

33:20.096 --> 33:21.973
...and stuck around
to make a phone call.

33:22.140 --> 33:24.600
Yeah, that's what the hookers
are saying.

33:24.809 --> 33:27.354
All right, give me the horn.

33:31.399 --> 33:36.237
- Sir! I'm ordering you to fully comply.
- I'm busy, all right. Come back later.

33:36.445 --> 33:39.739
<i>- Very good, Stu.
- Step out of the booth...</i>

33:39.948 --> 33:43.244
...and raise your hands.
I am giving you an order.

33:43.452 --> 33:45.744
<i>I give the orders here, Stu, don't I?</i>

33:45.995 --> 33:48.249
This guy is looking for us
to kill him, captain.

33:48.416 --> 33:50.918
Suicide by a cop?
Well, that's not gonna happen.

33:51.418 --> 33:53.044
Get that body out of here fast.

33:53.251 --> 33:55.545
Somebody get the body.
Tell the ambulance to get the body.

33:56.255 --> 34:00.385
<i>Thousands of people die every day,
but you put one dead body...</i>

34:00.594 --> 34:03.220
<i>... in the middle of a busy street
and it makes people crazy.</i>

34:03.429 --> 34:08.726
<i>Look at these guys.
You can smell the fear.</i>

34:09.018 --> 34:13.147
<i>- Ten cops.
- This reminds me of Nam.</i>

34:13.355 --> 34:15.398
<i>- Vietnam?
- Yes, Vietnam.</i>

34:15.607 --> 34:18.609
I was too young to go,
but I've seen pictures.

34:18.817 --> 34:22.614
<i>Well, pictures can't do it, Stu.
You can't imagine the fear, the stench.</i>

34:22.821 --> 34:26.493
<i>Napalm-charred bodies, children
leaving grenades in your boots.</i>

34:26.702 --> 34:30.161
<i>- Then you got blamed for the war.
- I came home and people spit on me.</i>

34:30.371 --> 34:32.581
Yeah, this country
owes you an apology.

34:32.790 --> 34:36.502
Look, I just had this vision of you,
of a kid, coming back from the war...

34:36.710 --> 34:40.295
...inured to the killing,
not able to get work, isolated.

34:40.504 --> 34:42.882
I think that could be made
into an affecting story...

34:43.091 --> 34:45.302
...and, you know, one
that everyone understands.

34:45.551 --> 34:47.929
And I think cops
are on the side of vets.

34:48.136 --> 34:51.516
<i>You are pathetic, Stu.
Why don't you wake up?</i>

34:51.725 --> 34:55.562
<i>Napalm-charred bodies?
I'd have to be 50 to be in that war!</i>

34:55.771 --> 34:57.562
Stop fucking with my head, please!

34:57.980 --> 34:58.981
I'm gonna go talk to him.

34:59.189 --> 35:00.858
Shouldn't we wait
on the ESU negotiator?

35:01.065 --> 35:04.278
They could take 20 minutes. I'm not
gonna take a chance on this one.

35:04.445 --> 35:05.779
I'm gonna handle this.

35:06.030 --> 35:10.200
Sir! I'm taking out my weapon.

35:10.409 --> 35:12.827
Putting my weapon down on the car.

35:13.036 --> 35:14.914
- The captain's going in.
- I'm not armed.

35:15.163 --> 35:18.249
- Yeah, neither am I.
- My name is Ramey.

35:18.458 --> 35:20.333
- Captain Ed Ramey.
- All right.

35:20.542 --> 35:22.336
- What's yours?
- I don't want to be friends.

35:22.586 --> 35:25.632
I don't know. It looks like
you could use a friend right now.

35:25.881 --> 35:28.593
<i>- Tell him you've already got a friend.
- I already got a friend.</i>

35:28.843 --> 35:29.844
Is that who you're
talking to on the phone?

35:32.138 --> 35:34.765
Look, I just want to hear
your side of it. That's all.

35:35.016 --> 35:38.227
I ain't got no side of it,
and I didn't shoot anybody.

35:38.477 --> 35:40.312
You see a fucking gun
anywhere? Look.

35:40.563 --> 35:43.188
It's in your back pocket!
I see it! He been...

35:44.982 --> 35:47.777
Sir, do you have the weapon
in your pocket?

35:48.070 --> 35:51.698
No. I got a cell phone and I got
cigarettes. I got no fucking weapon.

35:51.906 --> 35:54.533
Then what are you doing
in a phone booth making calls?

35:55.116 --> 35:57.120
- You want to see it? Here.
- Hey!

35:57.537 --> 35:59.290
Don't reach for that! Hold your fire!

36:00.580 --> 36:02.416
I don't need to see it.
I know what's there.

36:02.666 --> 36:05.960
I got plenty of witnesses over here
who saw you use it.

36:06.211 --> 36:08.045
They didn't see it
because it didn't happen!

36:08.297 --> 36:11.674
- Shut them up!
- He's dead, but it didn't happen?

36:11.925 --> 36:15.303
<i>- Then who did it?
- Mustn't tell him, Stu.</i>

36:15.511 --> 36:17.931
- I don't know.
- You were the closest one to him.

36:18.140 --> 36:20.309
- You must've saw it happen. Help me.
- No.

36:20.559 --> 36:24.188
<i>- This guy is getting on my nerves.
- Look, stay the fuck out of this.</i>

36:24.436 --> 36:26.272
Who do you keep talking to
on the phone?

36:26.563 --> 36:29.441
- Nobody.
- Your friend, your parent, your lover?

36:29.691 --> 36:33.321
<i>- Who?
- Careful, Stuart. Careful.</i>

36:33.570 --> 36:35.489
My psychiatrist.

36:35.697 --> 36:39.951
<i>- Excellent. I should've thought of that.
- I see. What's this doctor's name?</i>

36:40.160 --> 36:42.162
It would be really helpful to us
if we knew.

36:42.538 --> 36:45.999
He says not to tell you, all right?
It's privileged information.

36:46.206 --> 36:48.459
<i>Very good, Stuart.
See, now you're having fun.</i>

36:48.708 --> 36:52.256
- Yeah, whatever you fucking say.
- I respect your right to privacy.

36:52.548 --> 36:56.008
I've been through therapy myself.
The department provided it for me.

36:56.258 --> 36:59.553
I know it's not good form for a cop
to be saying that, but sometimes...

36:59.762 --> 37:03.933
...you know, circumstances, stress...
I had issues. I lost my marriage over it.

37:04.434 --> 37:06.769
<i>Tell him not to come any closer.</i>

37:07.102 --> 37:09.979
Don't come any closer. Stop there.
Go back a few steps.

37:10.270 --> 37:12.356
- Go back to where you were!
- Okay. No problem.

37:12.606 --> 37:16.236
- That's right.
- So you got some intimacy issues.

37:16.486 --> 37:20.113
I got those too. All I want to know is,
what happened, man?

37:20.364 --> 37:24.159
<i>- Tell him to read you your rights.
- I want you to read me my rights.</i>

37:24.411 --> 37:26.079
Stop asking questions.

37:26.788 --> 37:29.913
You have the right to remain silent.
You have the right to an attorney.

37:30.248 --> 37:33.710
If you cannot afford one,
an attorney will be provided for you.

37:33.919 --> 37:37.463
All right? So now, can you at least
give me your first name?

37:37.714 --> 37:39.633
<i>- Just your first name.
- Don't tell him.</i>

37:39.883 --> 37:43.093
It's my right
not to have any first name.

37:44.220 --> 37:46.055
- No gun, no name.
- That's right.

37:46.264 --> 37:49.726
<i>- You're highly underprivileged.
- Demand your lawyer.</i>

37:49.935 --> 37:51.601
And go get my lawyer too. All right?

37:51.852 --> 37:54.814
I want an attorney brought
down here to negotiate my surrender.

37:55.063 --> 37:57.483
<i>- Just brilliant, Stu.
- I understand that, but...</i>

37:57.692 --> 38:00.903
...it's gonna be difficult to get a lawyer
to come and risk his life.

38:01.153 --> 38:03.404
- Once you hand over the gun...
- How can I?

38:03.613 --> 38:05.698
You won't let me put my hand
in my pocket?

38:05.990 --> 38:08.952
We'll take it out for you.
All you have to do...

38:09.160 --> 38:13.164
...is step out with your hands raised.
Nothing will happen to you.

38:13.371 --> 38:15.290
<i>- It's not gonna work.
- Stu, Stu.</i>

38:15.541 --> 38:16.959
<i>- What?
- Ask him a question.</i>

38:17.209 --> 38:20.005
<i>Ask him if his wife
got tired of sleeping with him.</i>

38:20.212 --> 38:24.633
<i>- I... Fuck. I can't do that.
- Oh, sure you can, Stu.</i>

38:24.842 --> 38:27.552
<i>Ask him if he couldn't get it up,
if he couldn't satisfy her.</i>

38:27.803 --> 38:30.431
- Are you gonna step out of the booth?
- I can't. No.

38:30.638 --> 38:34.267
<i>- You're not stepping out of the booth?
- Ask him.</i>

38:34.476 --> 38:37.770
<i>- Is that a no?
- Ask him!</i>

38:38.228 --> 38:40.773
<i>- Both your lives depend on it.
- Sir?</i>

38:41.025 --> 38:47.612
Captain, you couldn't satisfy your wife
sexually?

38:51.242 --> 38:54.204
<i>- Excuse me?
- Ask him if he abuses himself now?</i>

38:54.454 --> 38:57.330
<i>- Does he masturbate on lonely nights?
- Fuck. For God's sake!</i>

38:57.956 --> 38:59.624
<i>Say it!</i>

38:59.874 --> 39:03.337
<i>Say it or I will blow him away!</i>

39:05.047 --> 39:08.258
- So do you whack off now?
- Hey!

39:12.721 --> 39:14.890
I'm gonna see about
that lawyer for you, okay?

39:15.141 --> 39:18.516
- Yes.
- Just relax.

39:20.228 --> 39:23.856
<i>- Stu, I think you hurt his feelings.
- I wanna know who's on that phone.</i>

39:24.106 --> 39:28.444
I want a techie here. I need
to talk to somebody about that phone.

39:28.693 --> 39:31.904
<i>Do you think we went too far, Stuart?
Should we give ourselves up?</i>

39:32.114 --> 39:34.450
<i>Maybe I'd like someone
to negotiate my surrender.</i>

39:34.658 --> 39:38.036
<i>- I'm sure we can work that out.
- I won't just spill my guts to anyone.</i>

39:38.245 --> 39:42.248
<i>Could you get me national news?
I mean, you've got connections, right?</i>

39:42.498 --> 39:44.917
<i>- Sure.
- Could you get Larry King down here?</i>

39:45.167 --> 39:47.003
Why the fuck would Larry King
come here?

39:47.212 --> 39:50.923
<i>Because you're friends.
Who else could you get, huh?</i>

39:51.172 --> 39:54.134
<i>Could you get Tom Brokaw?
How about Dan Rather? Diane Sawyer?</i>

39:54.385 --> 39:57.846
<i>- Look, I, I, I don't know. They're busy.
- I, I, I busy.</i>

39:58.097 --> 40:01.057
<i>How about Mike Wallace? Ted Koppel?
Peter Jennings? Katie Couric?</i>

40:01.267 --> 40:04.977
<i>Al Roker? Anybody? No! Nobody.</i>

40:05.226 --> 40:09.107
<i>Face it, Stu, you're smalltime.
And you've got a credibility problem.</i>

40:09.357 --> 40:12.068
Don't fucking worry about
my credibility! All right?

40:12.360 --> 40:14.111
What about yours?

40:14.320 --> 40:19.409
<i>Look, it's our friends from channels
two and five. Your local news, Stuart.</i>

40:19.617 --> 40:22.495
<i>You couldn't do this for your clients
if your life depended on it.</i>

40:22.746 --> 40:25.079
<i>But me, I've made you famous.</i>

40:25.330 --> 40:28.290
<i>Stick your head out so they can get
a better angle on you.</i>

40:28.542 --> 40:31.419
<i>- They're here to cover me dying.
- How ungrateful.</i>

40:31.670 --> 40:33.838
<i>Those cameras will make the police
very careful.</i>

40:34.047 --> 40:37.676
<i>- So come on, smile a little for them.
- Can you tap into that phone call?</i>

40:37.925 --> 40:39.593
- Should be no problem.
- Except...

40:39.804 --> 40:43.347
...we'll need a warrant
if he's on the line with his shrink.

40:43.557 --> 40:46.933
Fuck that. I'm not gonna
jeopardize this on a technicality.

40:47.183 --> 40:49.269
Look, tracing,
that's not a violation, right?

40:49.520 --> 40:52.648
- As long as we don't listen in.
- Okay, this is what I want you to do.

40:52.857 --> 40:55.901
I want you to find who he's talking to
and their current location.

40:56.109 --> 40:58.278
All right? We get that?

40:58.486 --> 41:00.739
I want somebody to find out
what's going on.

41:01.072 --> 41:05.160
<i>Look across the street and see what
everybody in New York is looking at.</i>

41:05.410 --> 41:08.370
<i>You're the man, Stuart.
You're the center of attention.</i>

41:08.662 --> 41:13.084
<i>Wait till this goes national:
ABC, CBS, CNN, UPN...</i>

41:13.333 --> 41:15.669
<i>You're gonna hit
the whole alphabet, Stu.</i>

41:16.253 --> 41:17.922
I'll be forgotten about in a week.

41:18.130 --> 41:20.381
No one ever remembers
the names of the victims.

41:20.590 --> 41:24.303
It's the killers that get the cover
of "Time" magazine. Right?

41:24.512 --> 41:28.766
Think about it. You'd be famous.
Ted Bundy, John Wayne Gacy...

41:29.015 --> 41:31.642
...fucking Jeffrey Dahmer.
Name a victim. You can't.

41:31.851 --> 41:34.562
Anyway, I don't deserve
to be the center of attention.

41:34.813 --> 41:38.108
- It ought to be you they're covering.
"- That attention would embarrass me".

41:38.316 --> 41:42.027
<i>- I know exactly the spin to put on this.
- How terror inspires your creativity?</i>

41:42.236 --> 41:46.074
Listen, this could be a media frenzy,
all right? You'd get Barbara Walters...

41:46.325 --> 41:48.576
...I mean, Larry King
if you still wanted him.

41:48.826 --> 41:53.496
<i>That approach seems predicated upon
me surrendering without killing you.</i>

41:54.914 --> 41:58.835
Listen, we can make you sympathetic,
sit with a writer, bang out a book.

41:59.085 --> 42:03.423
You know, movie of the week.
Get America on your side.

42:03.673 --> 42:06.550
All right, you killed Leon
because he was gonna kill me.

42:06.758 --> 42:09.637
You killed Leon to protect me.
All right?

42:09.888 --> 42:12.848
In a city where nobody looks out
for anybody, you took a stand.

42:13.099 --> 42:14.349
I'm your best witness.

42:14.598 --> 42:17.727
<i>So you want me to trust you
to get me out of this?</i>

42:17.936 --> 42:21.065
Yes, I do. I want you to trust me.
Trust me.

42:21.314 --> 42:25.319
<i>Stu, you must think I'm crazy.</i>

42:35.744 --> 42:38.704
- Oh, shit. Here comes Braman.
- I'll take care of him.

42:40.124 --> 42:43.252
Hey. Should've waited for me
to initiate contact with the suspect.

42:43.504 --> 42:45.670
I established a rapport.
Let you know if I need help.

42:45.921 --> 42:47.672
Are you grandstanding for TV cameras?

42:47.964 --> 42:50.676
Or do you want to leave this
to a professional?

42:50.884 --> 42:53.388
Until a professional gets here,
I'll handle it.

42:53.680 --> 42:58.098
You're a funny guy. All right, you get
somebody else killed, it's on your head.

42:58.308 --> 43:00.392
Got it?

43:00.644 --> 43:03.604
This is what I want to do, okay?
This is the City Hotel here.

43:03.854 --> 43:07.858
I want three guys in the lobby here.
And five sharpshooters up here.

43:08.109 --> 43:10.111
See if you can get me two
in the subway.

43:12.112 --> 43:14.282
What the fuck?

43:15.073 --> 43:18.201
<i>- Not going to answer it?
- I can't. I can't reach for the phone.</i>

43:18.410 --> 43:20.746
<i>- The cops will think it's a gun.
- I'll bet it's Kelly.</i>

43:20.995 --> 43:23.415
<i>She's probably heard what you did.
She's sick with worry.</i>

43:23.666 --> 43:25.751
I'm not gonna make her
feel any better, am I?

43:25.959 --> 43:28.420
<i>Well, you could ask her
to forgive you, Stuart.</i>

43:28.670 --> 43:33.758
<i>You could confess your sins
and beg for absolution, come clean.</i>

43:34.007 --> 43:36.553
<i>You're in this position
because you're not telling the truth.</i>

43:36.803 --> 43:38.638
I'm in this position
because you got a gun!

43:38.847 --> 43:43.516
<i>No. Stuart, that is the sin of spin.
Avoidance and deception.</i>

43:43.725 --> 43:48.313
<i>You're being given a chance here
to make things right. Now, talk to her.</i>

43:48.522 --> 43:52.526
<i>- Look, I can't. Please.
- I am telling you to answer that phone!</i>

43:52.817 --> 43:55.696
- Excuse me! Excuse me!
- You can't cross in front of here!

43:55.988 --> 43:57.907
<i>Answer it!</i>

43:58.740 --> 44:01.617
<i>- Look, I can't. Please.
- Don't make me hurt you!</i>

44:01.910 --> 44:04.328
<i>- Talk to your wife!
- It's not her calling.</i>

44:04.577 --> 44:10.961
<i>- How can you be so sure?
- It's you. It's you, you miserable fuck!</i>

44:11.210 --> 44:14.922
<i>Damn, you got me!
You continue to impress.</i>

44:15.131 --> 44:17.298
You could shoot me,
but you want them to do it!

44:17.549 --> 44:19.218
<i>- Yes, well, that's an option.
- Yeah.</i>

44:19.468 --> 44:20.970
- Captain.
- Yeah?

44:21.219 --> 44:23.554
This lady says the perp's her husband.
Here's her ID.

44:23.847 --> 44:26.891
- I couldn't believe when I saw this.
- Who do you think he's talking to?

44:27.183 --> 44:32.563
I don't know. I spoke to him
earlier today and I told him...

44:32.812 --> 44:35.608
...that there was a man who called me.
- A man?

44:35.817 --> 44:38.235
Did this upset him, that
you were talking to other men?

44:38.485 --> 44:42.281
Yes, he did seem a little upset,
but it's, no... It's not like that.

44:42.531 --> 44:46.367
- I didn't even know who this guy was.
- Who's his psychiatrist?

44:46.660 --> 44:49.203
- He doesn't have one.
- That you know of.

44:49.452 --> 44:53.292
I've been with him three years, married for
one. I'd know if he was in therapy.

44:53.540 --> 44:56.336
I wish to God he had been.
I saw somebody after my divorce.

44:56.586 --> 44:59.462
It kept me from picking up a gun,
doing something I would regret.

44:59.756 --> 45:03.051
- Look, Stu didn't kill anyone.
- Ma'am, under the circumstances...

45:03.259 --> 45:06.719
...you need to consider whether your
husband is who you thought he was.

45:07.012 --> 45:09.973
'Cause according to these witnesses
over here, he has a gun...

45:10.182 --> 45:13.560
...he has used that gun and let's pray
to God that he doesn't use it again.

45:13.810 --> 45:14.938
Captain?

45:15.188 --> 45:18.899
If you can think of any dispute
he's having currently, please, tell me.

45:19.150 --> 45:23.404
We're clearing City Hotel. I can stage
an assault unit within feet of the booth.

45:23.653 --> 45:27.116
We've also got sharpshooters
securing rooftop positions.

45:27.324 --> 45:29.657
- Let me know when you're in position.
- Absolutely.

45:29.824 --> 45:31.160
What about that wire tap?

45:31.411 --> 45:34.373
We're working on it.
You gotta hold tight a while, all right?

45:34.581 --> 45:37.291
- Yeah, no problem. No problem.
- Okay.

45:40.835 --> 45:43.631
Mrs. Shepard. Mrs. Shepard.

45:43.839 --> 45:46.799
- Does he like being called Stuart or Stu?
- Stu. Call him Stu.

45:47.050 --> 45:48.886
Stu. Okay.

45:49.136 --> 45:51.304
Come with me, please.

45:54.765 --> 45:56.685
Stu.

45:57.018 --> 45:58.269
I have your wife with me.

45:58.563 --> 46:01.188
<i>That's how you knew
she wasn't calling. You deceived me.</i>

46:01.397 --> 46:03.232
- Stu!
- She's not my wife.

46:03.524 --> 46:05.776
Are you okay?

46:06.569 --> 46:09.196
<i>- Can you just talk to me?
- Yes, talk to her, Stu.</i>

46:09.447 --> 46:10.864
Look, she's not my wife!

46:11.699 --> 46:15.493
She's some fucked-up, failed actress
I wouldn't handle. She's stalking me!

46:15.744 --> 46:18.622
You aren't making this up?
You are his wife, right?

46:18.830 --> 46:22.459
Yes, here's a photograph of us
together.

46:22.709 --> 46:25.128
I don't know what he's talking about.

46:25.337 --> 46:28.047
Stu. Listen to your wife.

46:28.297 --> 46:30.717
- She only wants what's best for you.
- She's not my wife!

46:31.760 --> 46:34.720
Stu, nobody wants to hurt you.

46:34.928 --> 46:38.305
- We just want to know what happened.
- Yeah, very good.

46:38.515 --> 46:42.937
Go home, you fucking lunatic!
You hear me? Go home!

46:43.145 --> 46:45.939
Please don't make things worse.
Just come out.

46:46.189 --> 46:48.191
Just do what they tell you to do.

46:48.483 --> 46:51.193
<i>Your wife is a crazy actress stalker
and you don't know her.</i>

46:51.403 --> 46:54.032
<i>- That's an interesting match.
- Get her out of here!</i>

46:54.280 --> 46:57.491
- Enough. I don't want to agitate this.
- You out of your fucking mind?

46:57.741 --> 47:01.204
- Come on, get the woman out of here!
- No. I don't know what's going on.

47:01.413 --> 47:07.043
He's bleeding... We... We're fine.
This morning everything was fine.

47:07.250 --> 47:09.253
You just stay here.
Just stay here, okay?

47:09.502 --> 47:12.549
- Okay.
- I think she did some good.

47:12.756 --> 47:15.551
- You got a number of that lawyer?
- No, we don't have a lawyer.

47:15.843 --> 47:18.553
He asked for his lawyer to come
negotiate his surrender.

47:19.012 --> 47:22.556
- Well, we never needed one.
- Well, you need a good one now.

47:22.766 --> 47:26.310
Look, you'll do me best
by staying near here. Okay?

47:26.603 --> 47:28.437
I'm gonna get your husband out alive.

47:28.646 --> 47:31.941
- I'm not going to let you fuck this up!
- Get Mrs. Shepard out of here.

47:32.191 --> 47:34.360
You know, get her some coffee
or something.

47:34.651 --> 47:37.531
You're gonna lose this guy.
You need some kind of redemption.

47:37.738 --> 47:40.782
- What are you seeing a shrink for?
- Get the fuck out of my face!

47:40.990 --> 47:44.535
- Don't fucking touch me!
- I'm not stepping down!

47:44.744 --> 47:46.998
You okay?

47:47.664 --> 47:50.375
Yeah, I'm fine.

47:50.917 --> 47:53.418
<i>You'd think she didn't know
she was being watched.</i>

47:53.711 --> 47:57.174
<i>- What?
- But beautiful women always know.</i>

47:57.424 --> 48:01.051
<i>- You talking about Kelly?
- That false indifference, superior air...</i>

48:01.301 --> 48:04.763
<i>... it's just a tease.
They want eyes on them.</i>

48:04.971 --> 48:08.267
<i>Why does she put on her makeup,
do her hair, dress so nicely?</i>

48:08.516 --> 48:10.601
<i>Not for her husband
that she hardly ever sees.</i>

48:10.852 --> 48:13.814
<i>No, it's for somebody else to notice.
I notice.</i>

48:14.189 --> 48:16.649
What are you doing?
Stay away from her. Leave her alone.

48:16.900 --> 48:18.902
<i>I'm giving her what she wants.</i>

48:19.153 --> 48:23.155
<i>I bet you've never looked at Kelly
the way I am right now.</i>

48:25.324 --> 48:28.537
<i>- Don't you dare fucking hurt her.
- Don't I dare?</i>

48:28.787 --> 48:30.621
<i>I'm not the one
who has hurt her, Stuart.</i>

48:30.872 --> 48:33.665
<i>What they can't know is what we do
to them in our minds. Right?</i>

48:33.915 --> 48:36.876
<i>- You sick fuck!
- The perfect violation.</i>

48:39.004 --> 48:40.923
<i>- Leave her out of this.
- How many times...</i>

48:41.131 --> 48:45.885
<i>... have you had sex with Pam
in that hotel bedroom in your head?</i>

48:46.094 --> 48:49.805
<i>Would you really miss Kelly
if she was gone?</i>

48:50.265 --> 48:53.644
That's it. Not another word.
I'm not talking to you.

48:53.892 --> 48:55.978
<i>Your choices put other people
in jeopardy.</i>

48:56.186 --> 48:59.148
<i>When are you gonna learn that?</i>

48:59.439 --> 49:03.153
<i>This is funny. Stuart, look uptown.</i>

49:03.361 --> 49:07.072
<i>These geniuses are still
at the juncture box trying to tap in.</i>

49:07.280 --> 49:10.742
<i>Only I have installed an encryption
device at both ends of the line.</i>

49:10.950 --> 49:12.620
<i>There's no chance of a trap trace...</i>

49:12.828 --> 49:17.582
<i>... so now they've gotta try some fancy
LoJack instrument. It's really sad.</i>

49:17.832 --> 49:20.794
<i>I hope you weren't
pinning your hopes on those morons.</i>

49:21.042 --> 49:23.921
<i>Truth is, I'm on a wireless A.D.S.
With a cloned number.</i>

49:24.131 --> 49:28.216
<i>It'll take a half an hour to find out
I call forwarded through Philadelphia.</i>

49:28.425 --> 49:32.846
<i>And let me tell you, this will all be over
before they can get a dial tone.</i>

49:33.138 --> 49:36.516
We can't get a trace or break into the
line. It's like a ball of rubber bands.

49:36.768 --> 49:40.144
I knew there was something weird
about this. You keep working on it.

49:47.276 --> 49:50.570
<i>Stu. Stuart, come on,
you're behaving like a child.</i>

49:50.780 --> 49:52.531
<i>Still gonna give me
the silent treatment?</i>

49:52.781 --> 49:56.786
<i>Hello. Stuart, don't do this, please.
Come on.</i>

49:56.994 --> 49:59.622
<i>My sainted mother used to do this.
She used to dish this out.</i>

49:59.872 --> 50:02.332
<i>Stuart, please don't do this.</i>

50:02.582 --> 50:05.795
<i>Stuart, you're bringing back
my unhappy childhood.</i>

50:06.004 --> 50:11.173
<i>Stuart, talk to me! Please, talk to me!
I can't take it! Stu, please...</i>

50:12.092 --> 50:14.592
<i>I'm kidding.
I had a very happy childhood.</i>

50:14.845 --> 50:19.265
<i>Hey, there's our girl again.
I wasn't planning on killing her...</i>

50:19.515 --> 50:22.017
<i>... but plans change.</i>

50:22.894 --> 50:24.896
Just tell me
what the fuck you want from me.

50:25.105 --> 50:29.275
<i>Hello. There you are.
I thought I was talking to myself again.</i>

50:29.483 --> 50:31.987
Anything you want. I'll do it.
Just tell me.

50:32.237 --> 50:37.782
<i>Tell Kelly about the real Stu,
about your little motel.</i>

50:37.991 --> 50:42.246
<i>- And then you'll let us go?
- Why not?</i>

50:45.415 --> 50:47.334
<i>- Kelly!
- That's a start.</i>

50:47.542 --> 50:49.128
- Baby!
- Hold her back!

50:49.377 --> 50:50.628
- Hey!
- Talk to me!

50:50.879 --> 50:53.131
- Grab her! Keep her back!
- Yes?

50:53.382 --> 50:54.548
I'm listening.

50:56.132 --> 50:57.634
Kelly, I called some woman.

50:58.761 --> 51:01.097
<i>- Every day.
- Every day.</i>

51:01.305 --> 51:05.724
I was attracted to this other woman.
And I called her and...

51:05.977 --> 51:12.107
<i>- I wanted to fuck her.
- And I wanted to sleep with her.</i>

51:13.233 --> 51:18.695
<i>No. I wanted to fuck her.</i>

51:21.282 --> 51:27.079
<i>- Say it. Say it!
- And I wanted to fuck her.</i>

51:27.329 --> 51:33.378
- I'm sorry.
- Whatever you did, I don't care.

51:33.628 --> 51:36.839
Please, just come out of the booth.
Okay?

51:37.046 --> 51:41.633
That's all I did. That's all I did.
I'm sorry.

51:44.304 --> 51:47.848
All right, I've done what you asked.
That's it. I've had enough of this.

51:48.182 --> 51:50.268
<i>I haven't.</i>

51:50.518 --> 51:55.607
<i>- You said you'd let us go.
- I changed my mind.</i>

51:55.982 --> 51:58.858
You miserable fuck. You can't do this.
You can't do this to me.

51:59.109 --> 52:02.570
Look, I took all your shit.
I did everything you fucking asked.

52:02.821 --> 52:04.322
You lied to me.
I'm done with this.

52:04.530 --> 52:08.702
I've fucking had enough.
You can go fuck yourself! Later.

52:09.119 --> 52:11.370
- He hung up.
- Maybe they already got a trace.

52:11.622 --> 52:14.249
ESU, ESU?

52:17.836 --> 52:19.671
- I'm giving myself up!
- He's coming out!

52:19.879 --> 52:22.423
- Heads up!
- I want to see you toss away your weapon!

52:22.839 --> 52:25.466
Throw the weapon outside the booth!
Stay where you are!

52:26.051 --> 52:28.930
- First, the weapon!
- Don't hurt him! Please, don't hurt him!

52:29.178 --> 52:31.682
- There's no fucking gun!
- Stay right where you are!

52:31.933 --> 52:36.686
I want you to turn around. Interlock
your fingers behind your head. Okay?

52:38.397 --> 52:42.026
- Please give them the gun!
- Kelly, no!

52:42.818 --> 52:45.527
Get back! Kelly!

52:46.571 --> 52:48.489
- Freeze!
- Get back! Get back!

52:48.740 --> 52:50.575
- Get back!
- Okay! Okay!

52:53.452 --> 52:54.787
I gotta answer it.

52:55.080 --> 52:56.914
Freeze! Don't move.

52:57.579 --> 52:59.415
Hold your fire!

53:00.960 --> 53:03.378
Hold your fire!

53:03.796 --> 53:06.048
Hold your fire.

53:08.091 --> 53:11.302
- Hold. Hold.
- Please.

53:12.303 --> 53:15.431
- Go ahead. Answer it.
- What the fuck are you doing?

53:15.682 --> 53:17.433
He's coming out!

53:18.059 --> 53:19.308
Answer the phone.

53:24.356 --> 53:26.900
<i>- You fucking coward.
- Hi, Stu.</i>

53:27.151 --> 53:30.945
<i>Now, you've had your little tantrum
and you said some things in anger...</i>

53:31.195 --> 53:33.363
<i>... that I am willing to forget.</i>

53:34.783 --> 53:37.202
Get her back in the car!
I want her in the car.

53:37.451 --> 53:40.163
If he's not the shooter,
then who the fuck is?

53:44.043 --> 53:46.295
Captain, what the fuck
is up with the phone calls?

53:46.585 --> 53:48.171
<i>- So can we start over?
- You lied.</i>

53:48.380 --> 53:51.590
<i>You can't know the pain of betrayal
until you've been betrayed.</i>

53:51.839 --> 53:54.551
Sniper in one of these buildings.
I want you to talk to ESU.

53:54.760 --> 53:57.096
I want you to get one of these guys,
this building.

53:57.346 --> 54:01.682
Start looking up there from window
to window till you find the perp. Okay?

54:01.891 --> 54:05.813
I want you to do it quickly, and
I want you to do it quietly. All right?

54:08.023 --> 54:09.357
Where's the ESU sergeant?

54:09.732 --> 54:11.067
You said we could go.

54:11.359 --> 54:13.361
<i>- You said you'd let us go.
- Relax, Stuart.</i>

54:13.609 --> 54:15.529
<i>Nobody gets it right the first time.</i>

54:15.738 --> 54:19.199
<i>You've done better than others.
You will get a chance to end this.</i>

54:19.450 --> 54:21.869
<i>- I'm just not finished yet.
- Yeah, well, I am.</i>

54:22.119 --> 54:24.288
<i>- There's nothing keeping me.
- Besides the fear of death?</i>

54:24.495 --> 54:26.831
I dive out and you've got one shot.
I'm gonna be dancing.

54:27.041 --> 54:30.419
<i>- You think you can get me?
- I could go for some target practice.</i>

54:30.669 --> 54:33.212
One shot, they look for you.
Second shot, you give yourself away.

54:33.463 --> 54:35.298
<i>Go on, Stuart, hang up!</i>

54:35.548 --> 54:38.676
<i>Trust your fate to friendly men in flak
jackets with automatic weapons.</i>

54:39.218 --> 54:43.222
<i>I'm sure you can patch up that little
misunderstanding about the dead body.</i>

54:43.431 --> 54:45.849
<i>- Cops can't prove I killed anyone.
- You had motive.</i>

54:46.058 --> 54:48.478
<i>- No weapon.
- Plenty of loudmouth witnesses.</i>

54:48.728 --> 54:49.854
No gun and I walk.

54:50.105 --> 54:51.939
<i>- Are you sure?
- Yes!</i>

54:52.148 --> 54:56.401
<i>Yeah? You murder a guy and you
forget where you stashed your gun?</i>

54:56.610 --> 54:59.572
<i>Why don't you lift the
plastic ceiling panel and feel around?</i>

55:02.073 --> 55:04.159
<i>Peekaboo!</i>

55:09.539 --> 55:12.917
<i>What's up next to the florescent bulb?
Check it out, Stu.</i>

55:13.167 --> 55:15.626
Cops see me reach for something,
they'll blow me away.

55:15.918 --> 55:17.420
<i>There's only one way to find out.</i>

55:17.671 --> 55:21.216
Look, the slugs in that dead guy,
they came from your rifle.

55:21.425 --> 55:24.302
They're not gonna match a handgun.
I've seen enough cop shows.

55:24.511 --> 55:27.722
<i>Hollow points fragment on impact,
Stuart. There's nothing to match.</i>

55:27.972 --> 55:30.601
<i>- Only there's no gun up there.
- Don't take my word for it.</i>

55:30.809 --> 55:34.813
<i>See for yourself.
There are rounds left in it.</i>

55:35.104 --> 55:37.899
<i>- I totally couldn't give a shit.
- Come on. Don't disappoint me.</i>

55:38.149 --> 55:41.610
<i>Use your imagination. You'd shoot me
if you got the chance, wouldn't you?</i>

55:41.860 --> 55:44.907
With a big fucking smile on my face.

55:45.114 --> 55:47.533
<i>There's the spirit.</i>

55:47.784 --> 55:51.244
<i>Now, what if I told you I was just
above the theater, four floors up?</i>

55:51.453 --> 55:54.081
<i>See the pink curtains?</i>

55:54.415 --> 55:56.834
<i>There you go, Stuart. Yes.</i>

55:57.085 --> 55:58.669
<i>Yoo-hoo!</i>

55:58.878 --> 56:01.294
<i>Yoo-hoo!</i>

56:05.299 --> 56:07.052
Why would you do that?

56:07.301 --> 56:11.890
<i>Because it's fun.
The odds are even now, Stuart.</i>

56:12.181 --> 56:13.933
<i>Isn't that what you wanted?</i>

56:14.225 --> 56:16.769
<i>You know where I am,
and you have a gun.</i>

56:17.020 --> 56:21.355
<i>If you have it in you,
you can take me down.</i>

56:23.524 --> 56:24.860
Fuck!

56:25.068 --> 56:29.156
<i>- They'd kill me before I got a shot.
- Oh, you're probably right.</i>

56:29.406 --> 56:30.740
<i>I'm not really there anyway.</i>

56:31.033 --> 56:34.828
<i>You would've just spoiled
some nice lady's curtains.</i>

56:38.540 --> 56:41.751
<i>Looks like someone watches the news.</i>

56:43.210 --> 56:46.838
<i>- Who?
- The motel.</i>

56:48.841 --> 56:51.718
<i>- Oh, God.
- I think she could use a new headshot.</i>

56:51.927 --> 56:54.179
<i>- Don't!
- Then take down the gun.</i>

56:54.470 --> 56:58.183
<i>- Look, this has nothing to do with her!
- She has everything to do with this.</i>

56:58.391 --> 57:00.937
<i>You're here and she's here
because you called her.</i>

57:01.186 --> 57:05.439
<i>Now, take it down!
Don't make me hurt Pam, Stuart.</i>

57:05.730 --> 57:07.899
<i>- Take down the gun!
- Hey, everybody, get ready.</i>

57:08.150 --> 57:10.862
Hold on, hold on.
Let's just see what he does, all right?

57:11.153 --> 57:12.406
Let's see what he's doing.

57:16.866 --> 57:18.119
There's nothing there.

57:18.369 --> 57:22.081
<i>Nothing but your fingerprints on the
finest cop killer money can buy.</i>

57:22.332 --> 57:26.208
<i>- Come on, Stu. Let's see it.
- Fuck, no! It's staying there.</i>

57:26.459 --> 57:28.544
<i>Fine, then someone
will have to take your place.</i>

57:28.793 --> 57:31.045
<i>Come on, Stu,
you're in a perfect position.</i>

57:31.339 --> 57:33.840
<i>- How do you figure?
- You get to choose between them.</i>

57:34.133 --> 57:38.553
<i>Pamela or Kelly? Should I choose?
One of them can take your place.</i>

57:38.846 --> 57:40.514
Don't do this!

57:40.722 --> 57:44.520
<i>You've got to be more in touch with your
feelings. I thought you only loved Kelly!</i>

57:44.727 --> 57:46.647
<i>- It's true!
- But you lie to her.</i>

57:46.854 --> 57:48.188
It's complicated.

57:48.438 --> 57:51.983
<i>Then I'll uncomplicate it, Stuart,
by removing temptation. I say Pam.</i>

57:52.192 --> 57:54.819
No! Look, this isn't Pam's fault.
This is all my fault!

57:55.028 --> 57:56.280
She's innocent!

57:57.363 --> 58:01.702
<i>Ticktock, ticktock.
Time's running out. Okay, Kelly, then.</i>

58:01.951 --> 58:03.284
<i>- You decide.
- No, please!</i>

58:03.537 --> 58:06.165
<i>Come on, Stu.
Don't you get the game yet?</i>

58:06.414 --> 58:09.292
<i>You're a selfish guy.
Pick one and save yourself.</i>

58:10.249 --> 58:12.669
<i>Blond or brunette? Time's running out.</i>

58:12.918 --> 58:16.716
<i>You or them? Kelly or Pam?
Kelly or Pam?</i>

58:16.924 --> 58:19.092
Come on, Stu!

58:19.343 --> 58:21.594
Stop this.

58:21.886 --> 58:25.013
<i>- I can't take this anymore.
- What are you doing? Get up!</i>

58:25.223 --> 58:27.935
<i>- I was looking for my ring. Look...
- Get up, Stuart!</i>

58:28.143 --> 58:32.479
<i>Stand up and be a man.
You're embarrassing yourself.</i>

58:35.482 --> 58:36.817
Captain! I got it. Listen.

58:37.026 --> 58:41.780
The rifleman reports subject pulled
a small, dark object out of his pocket.

58:42.072 --> 58:44.950
All right. You're looking at a suicide
on national fucking TV.

58:45.201 --> 58:46.953
You gonna let me take this over?

58:47.202 --> 58:49.372
Tell everybody to hold on,
to hold their fire.

58:49.623 --> 58:52.750
Everybody hold. Stay ready, but hold.

58:53.540 --> 58:58.128
<i>- Stuart, you're beginning to annoy me.
- You can't do this.</i>

58:58.379 --> 59:02.383
<i>Stu.
No more spinning, no more excuses.</i>

59:04.385 --> 59:07.428
What're you doing? Look, listen.
Listen, please listen to me.

59:07.637 --> 59:08.890
<i>No more delays, Stuart.</i>

59:09.140 --> 59:11.601
Look... I'm on my knees
begging you not to kill me.

59:11.851 --> 59:14.187
<i>I will if you keep up
this pathetic spectacle.</i>

59:14.437 --> 59:16.354
Excuse me! He's on the phone, talking.

59:16.563 --> 59:18.982
From up in your high window,
you could kill anyone.

59:19.231 --> 59:22.027
<i>- Yes, I know that, Stuart.
- All right, and...</i>

59:22.236 --> 59:24.653
You could pick off any of the cops,
with your rifle.

59:24.862 --> 59:26.531
<i>Shut up and stand up!</i>

59:26.739 --> 59:28.742
Look, why threaten Kelly?

59:28.909 --> 59:31.369
You liked how she sounded
on the phone at the store.

59:31.619 --> 59:34.080
Please don't hurt her.
Don't fucking hurt my wife.

59:34.331 --> 59:37.207
<i>This doesn't have to end with me
shooting you. You leave no choice.</i>

59:37.415 --> 59:40.211
<i>- Now, get up!
- All right.</i>

59:40.669 --> 59:44.298
Okay, how does this end?
Tell me how this ends.

59:44.505 --> 59:46.259
<i>The stage is almost set.</i>

59:46.507 --> 59:49.719
<i>People are gonna be eating dinner
watching you die.</i>

59:50.054 --> 59:53.098
We got a sniper situation here.

59:53.432 --> 59:55.268
What about that phone call
to your store?

59:55.475 --> 59:58.518
I got a phone call this afternoon.
I think it was a prank call.

59:58.810 --> 01:00:01.439
He told me Stu would be calling me
from a phone booth.

01:00:01.729 --> 01:00:03.899
How long will it take
to get a record of her calls?

01:00:04.107 --> 01:00:06.902
If he's using that secure line,
we won't know more than now.

01:00:07.153 --> 01:00:10.864
Say he didn't. Let's assume he's
a human, makes mistakes like all of us.

01:00:11.115 --> 01:00:14.244
I need to get that number.
I've been waiting for that number.

01:00:14.494 --> 01:00:17.538
It was a guy.
He sounded like mid-30's.

01:00:17.788 --> 01:00:21.415
Mrs. Shepard? It would be safer
if you got back in the car, okay?

01:00:21.664 --> 01:00:23.500
- Please get back in the car.
- Thank you.

01:00:23.707 --> 01:00:27.255
I want you to divert incoming ESU
units to Broadway and hold them there.

01:00:27.464 --> 01:00:29.550
- Want me to clear the streets?
- Yeah.

01:00:29.758 --> 01:00:33.218
No, no, no. I don't want the sniper
to be aware of any of our movements.

01:00:33.469 --> 01:00:35.053
He's already got position on us.

01:00:35.305 --> 01:00:37.723
Let's not let him know
we know too much, okay?

01:00:38.641 --> 01:00:40.476
- Hey, Jonah.
- Yeah.

01:00:40.726 --> 01:00:42.226
Don't look up.

01:00:45.229 --> 01:00:47.399
Get me sharpshooters
looking at those windows.

01:00:47.649 --> 01:00:50.151
- You got it, captain.
- I'm gonna buy us some time here.

01:00:50.402 --> 01:00:51.902
All right.

01:00:58.452 --> 01:01:01.495
Stu! It's okay if I come out
and talk to you for a second?

01:01:01.747 --> 01:01:03.498
<i>- I don't know.
- This guy is so lonely.</i>

01:01:04.331 --> 01:01:08.126
<i>- All he wants to do is talk.
- You're walking through a bad dream...</i>

01:01:08.334 --> 01:01:11.296
<i>...and you can't wake up.
- Now he's really testing my patience.</i>

01:01:11.505 --> 01:01:13.507
You wanna wake up, Stu?

01:01:13.715 --> 01:01:18.720
I wanna, but I got issues
I can't talk about.

01:01:18.927 --> 01:01:23.850
- That your psychiatrist on the phone?
- Yeah, yeah. I'm paying him overtime.

01:01:24.142 --> 01:01:27.101
That was pretty brave what you did.

01:01:27.769 --> 01:01:30.564
I mean,
admitting all that stuff to your wife.

01:01:30.773 --> 01:01:34.234
- It was liberating, right?
- Should've been.

01:01:34.444 --> 01:01:37.487
Maybe if I could be more honest
with my wife then...

01:01:37.654 --> 01:01:40.282
...I don't know,
something would've turned out different.

01:01:40.532 --> 01:01:42.201
<i>Oh, please.</i>

01:01:42.410 --> 01:01:46.120
- Trust is the key. You trust me, Stu?
"- Get this man a seat on" Oprah.

01:01:46.329 --> 01:01:50.165
I wanna, but I got the issues
I can't talk about.

01:01:50.415 --> 01:01:52.751
<i>Yes, lethal issues.
Tell him to stay back.</i>

01:01:53.003 --> 01:01:55.005
Look, don't come any closer.

01:01:55.254 --> 01:01:57.882
Hey, I don't wanna cause
or make anything harder for you.

01:01:58.132 --> 01:02:01.760
<i>Pam, Ramey, Kelly, people on the
street, you've got lives in your hands.</i>

01:02:02.136 --> 01:02:05.181
I told you it's a private conversation.
What the fuck do you want?

01:02:05.473 --> 01:02:08.933
I wanna let you know that it's safe
outside the booth.

01:02:09.184 --> 01:02:11.352
<i>- It's not.
- It's always, "Get out of the booth! "</i>

01:02:11.560 --> 01:02:14.355
I like it in the fucking booth!
All right? It's my world.

01:02:14.564 --> 01:02:16.983
This is my booth, and
I'm not coming out. All right?

01:02:17.275 --> 01:02:19.027
- Never.
- We're not gonna force you out...

01:02:19.569 --> 01:02:21.822
...because there could be
some miscalculation...

01:02:21.987 --> 01:02:25.201
...and then I would never find out
why this happened.

01:02:25.951 --> 01:02:31.663
Stu, I'm afraid. I'm afraid
that I'm gonna be standing by...

01:02:31.871 --> 01:02:35.792
...and my men are gonna shoot
some guy...

01:02:36.042 --> 01:02:42.342
...and when we find out what's in his
hand, once we turn over his body...

01:02:42.591 --> 01:02:45.093
...and we see what he was
threatening people with...

01:02:45.302 --> 01:02:48.680
We realize that it was just
a little black Bible.

01:02:49.222 --> 01:02:53.017
<i>- Or a cell phone.
- Don't push me, Stu.</i>

01:02:56.437 --> 01:02:58.105
I'm not gonna let that happen here.

01:02:58.647 --> 01:03:00.732
I wanted to make a phone call.
One lousy call...

01:03:00.983 --> 01:03:02.985
<i>That's enough, Stu.</i>

01:03:03.236 --> 01:03:07.490
- You got some bad news on that call?
- The worst.

01:03:07.780 --> 01:03:09.700
I bet you want to jump off the edge.

01:03:10.951 --> 01:03:13.579
<i>- I've been falling ever since.
- I'm gonna push him over the edge.</i>

01:03:13.828 --> 01:03:15.329
<i>Just say the word.</i>

01:03:15.538 --> 01:03:16.956
It's time to land.

01:03:17.456 --> 01:03:20.834
- When you hit bottom, you die.
- I'm your safety net.

01:03:21.043 --> 01:03:24.005
<i>Oh, please, say the word.</i>

01:03:24.255 --> 01:03:27.466
If I tell you what you wanna know,
you'll die too.

01:03:27.715 --> 01:03:29.885
<i>Exactly.</i>

01:03:32.846 --> 01:03:34.516
- I'm going.
- Good.

01:03:36.558 --> 01:03:39.768
But, Stu, we put a call out
to your lawyer.

01:03:40.019 --> 01:03:42.105
Your wife, she gave us the number.

01:03:43.441 --> 01:03:50.029
And I got my best men working
on bringing him down. Okay?

01:03:50.863 --> 01:03:52.783
<i>That's it. The captain gets a bullet.</i>

01:03:53.324 --> 01:03:54.743
Get out of here!
Hear what I said, asshole?

01:03:54.950 --> 01:03:59.036
<i>- Get out of here, go on, now! Go!
- Enough of this sideshow, Stu.</i>

01:03:59.287 --> 01:04:03.291
<i>- Your sins have caught up to you.
- So this is all some religious thing?</i>

01:04:03.458 --> 01:04:06.919
<i>That explains it. Bible-crazed killer
picks on fashion-obsessed PR guy.</i>

01:04:07.170 --> 01:04:09.591
<i>- Tell me what you want, then.
- What everyone wants...</i>

01:04:09.799 --> 01:04:12.049
<i>... for the bad guy
to get what he deserves.</i>

01:04:12.258 --> 01:04:14.344
<i>Go for the gun.</i>

01:04:14.595 --> 01:04:16.679
<i>- Kill myself?
- Yes.</i>

01:04:16.888 --> 01:04:19.057
It would be a rare, unselfish act.

01:04:23.768 --> 01:04:26.396
- We got hostile action.
- Nothing is hostile until I say it is.

01:04:27.106 --> 01:04:29.441
<i>- Look, I can't find it.
- Kelly, Pam, bam! Bam!</i>

01:04:29.650 --> 01:04:31.735
All right! Look, I found it. I got it.

01:04:31.986 --> 01:04:35.030
<i>- Then let's see it. Let everyone see it.
- The cops'll kill me.</i>

01:04:35.280 --> 01:04:38.743
<i>Yes.
You're talking prime-time material now.</i>

01:04:38.993 --> 01:04:40.828
<i>- All this shit just to watch me die?
- No.</i>

01:04:41.078 --> 01:04:46.248
<i>To get you to do what's right.
If you wanna save yourself, confess.</i>

01:04:46.499 --> 01:04:48.960
<i>- I already told Kelly everything.
- Everything?</i>

01:04:49.209 --> 01:04:52.170
<i>No. No more excuses
and half-truths, Stuart.</i>

01:04:52.421 --> 01:04:56.216
<i>You look out into those cameras
and you bare your soul.</i>

01:04:56.466 --> 01:04:59.096
<i>TV seems to help bring out
the worst in people.</i>

01:04:59.345 --> 01:05:01.014
<i>You should be fine.</i>

01:05:01.263 --> 01:05:04.641
- How're those techs doing? Anything?
- No, not yet. Not yet.

01:05:04.933 --> 01:05:09.354
We haven't found your lawyer yet,
Stu. But we're getting close. Okay?

01:05:09.562 --> 01:05:13.733
<i>Stuart, I'm offering you a chance
to redeem yourself.</i>

01:05:14.067 --> 01:05:16.611
<i>Come on, humble yourself
in front of your loved ones...</i>

01:05:16.861 --> 01:05:21.283
<i>... and millions of strangers and me.
It's do-or-die time.</i>

01:05:21.531 --> 01:05:23.618
What, you couldn't find anyone
worse than me?

01:05:23.868 --> 01:05:26.828
Not a murderer or a child molester
but a publicist...

01:05:27.036 --> 01:05:29.371
...who has fantasies
about pretty little actresses.

01:05:29.832 --> 01:05:32.252
Who spends money on Italian suits
and dry cleaning...

01:05:32.500 --> 01:05:35.795
...so people think he's important.
Who doesn't waste time being nice...

01:05:36.046 --> 01:05:38.381
...to people who are of no use to him.
These are my crimes?

01:05:38.547 --> 01:05:43.636
<i>Stuart, I know your crimes. Tell them.</i>

01:06:07.701 --> 01:06:10.119
I've never done anything for anybody...

01:06:10.410 --> 01:06:12.913
...who couldn't do something for me.
I string along...

01:06:13.205 --> 01:06:16.334
...a kid with promises
that I'll pay him money.

01:06:16.584 --> 01:06:18.670
I keep him around because he
looks up to me.

01:06:18.837 --> 01:06:23.091
Adam, if you're watching, don't be
a publicist. You're too good for it.

01:06:23.258 --> 01:06:29.221
I lie in person and on the phone.
I lie to my friends.

01:06:29.430 --> 01:06:33.599
I lie to newspapers and magazines who
sell my lies to more and more people.

01:06:33.808 --> 01:06:39.105
I'm just a part of a big cycle of lies.
I should be fucking president.

01:06:39.355 --> 01:06:43.859
I wear all this Italian shit because
underneath, I still feel like the Bronx.

01:06:44.151 --> 01:06:46.696
I think I need these clothes,
and this watch.

01:06:46.987 --> 01:06:51.660
My $2000 watch is a fake,
and so am I.

01:06:52.032 --> 01:06:54.912
I neglected the things
I should've valued most.

01:06:55.203 --> 01:06:56.954
I valued this shit.

01:06:57.998 --> 01:07:04.296
I take off my wedding ring to call Pam.
Kelly, that's Pam.

01:07:06.088 --> 01:07:08.342
- Somebody got a 20 on this Pam?
- Don't blame her.

01:07:08.592 --> 01:07:10.844
I never told her if I was married,
and if I did...

01:07:11.094 --> 01:07:12.763
...she would've told me to go home.

01:07:14.680 --> 01:07:19.016
Kelly, looking at you now,
I'm ashamed of myself.

01:07:20.895 --> 01:07:26.775
I mean, I work so hard on this image,
on Stu Shepard, the asshole...

01:07:26.983 --> 01:07:31.906
...who refers to himself in third person,
that I only proved I should be alone.

01:07:32.991 --> 01:07:36.785
I've been dressing up as something
I'm not for so long...

01:07:37.035 --> 01:07:40.663
...I'm so afraid you won't like what's
underneath.

01:07:40.872 --> 01:07:46.003
But here I am.
I'm just flesh and blood and weakness.

01:07:48.504 --> 01:07:50.255
I love you so fucking much.

01:07:56.553 --> 01:08:02.016
I take off this ring because it only
reminds me of how I've failed you.

01:08:02.265 --> 01:08:05.146
And, I don't wanna give you up.

01:08:05.354 --> 01:08:09.440
I wanna make things better,
but it may not be my choice anymore.

01:08:10.274 --> 01:08:12.819
You deserve better.

01:08:28.250 --> 01:08:31.627
<i>- You're not gonna let me go.
- No.</i>

01:08:31.837 --> 01:08:35.631
You never were.
I know a thing about lies.

01:08:35.841 --> 01:08:37.759
I know a thing or two
about liars as well.

01:08:37.968 --> 01:08:40.676
<i>Then why the confession?</i>

01:08:46.768 --> 01:08:49.185
I didn't do it for you.

01:08:51.020 --> 01:08:53.023
- Right there.
- Yeah, got that.

01:08:53.273 --> 01:08:57.194
Captain, captain. The call to his wife
originated at 2: 17...

01:08:57.444 --> 01:08:59.779
...at a hard line from the old
Barkley Hotel.

01:08:59.988 --> 01:09:02.158
- You got a room?
- 604.

01:09:02.613 --> 01:09:05.158
Second window from the corner.
ESU units holding.

01:09:05.785 --> 01:09:07.285
Bring them in from 52nd Street.

01:09:07.537 --> 01:09:10.913
Cover the windows, doors, fire escape,
every goddamn point of exit.

01:09:11.165 --> 01:09:13.960
- ESU, ESU, come in from the 52nd...
- Stu!

01:09:14.251 --> 01:09:16.877
- Your lawyer's coming down now!
- Doors, fire escapes...

01:09:17.129 --> 01:09:18.381
Now!

01:09:19.131 --> 01:09:21.384
<i>At least you'll die
with a clean conscience.</i>

01:09:21.593 --> 01:09:24.886
No, you're the one that's gonna die!
Listen, you can hear them now.

01:09:25.136 --> 01:09:26.804
They're coming to get you. Know why?

01:09:27.013 --> 01:09:29.348
<i>- Because I sent them!
- You can't stop lying, can you?</i>

01:09:29.599 --> 01:09:31.684
I can't stop lying?
They're coming up the stairs.

01:09:31.892 --> 01:09:33.562
They're coming to get you.
Look around.

01:09:33.810 --> 01:09:35.647
That room's getting smaller
every second.

01:09:35.897 --> 01:09:37.229
Inch by inch! You know what?

01:09:37.439 --> 01:09:40.234
It's not gonna be any bigger
than this fucking goddamn booth!

01:09:40.527 --> 01:09:43.029
- They're in position, in position.
- Get them to move!

01:09:49.702 --> 01:09:51.537
<i>- There's nobody there.
- There's nobody there?</i>

01:09:51.746 --> 01:09:54.539
They're coming through that fucking
door to put you out of your misery.

01:09:54.790 --> 01:09:57.251
You got a couple seconds left.
What're you gonna do?

01:09:57.501 --> 01:10:00.127
<i>If this is true, I have to take someone
with me, don't I?</i>

01:10:00.377 --> 01:10:03.757
<i>Since Kelly is the most important thing
in your life, I'll take her.</i>

01:10:04.006 --> 01:10:06.468
Then take me! Take me.
This is about me!

01:10:07.260 --> 01:10:09.886
I'm the fucking one you want!
Take me!

01:10:10.095 --> 01:10:12.598
This is about me! Come on!

01:10:12.890 --> 01:10:14.809
Take me! It's me you want!

01:10:51.383 --> 01:10:53.552
This is Captain Ramey.
Somebody talk to me.

01:10:53.845 --> 01:10:55.847
<i>We're too late.
The psycho heard us coming...</i>

01:10:56.097 --> 01:10:58.017
<i>... and slashed his throat
with a knife.</i>

01:10:58.224 --> 01:11:01.603
<i>- What's his condition?
- Critical. He's lost a lot of blood.</i>

01:11:01.811 --> 01:11:04.230
Get him down here.
I don't want nobody dying on me.

01:11:04.437 --> 01:11:05.857
All right.

01:11:07.026 --> 01:11:09.444
- Kelly, where's Kelly?
- Your wife's fine, all right?

01:11:09.694 --> 01:11:11.529
All right, try not to sit up.

01:11:13.571 --> 01:11:15.740
- What hit me?
- Rubber bullet.

01:11:15.949 --> 01:11:18.994
Figured if somebody's gonna
shoot you, it might as well be us.

01:11:19.245 --> 01:11:21.330
Thanks.

01:11:21.663 --> 01:11:23.664
- Did you get him?
- You did.

01:11:24.167 --> 01:11:26.627
- I didn't do anything.
- Give yourself some credit.

01:11:26.876 --> 01:11:30.255
Got yourself out alive.
Doesn't always happen that way.

01:11:33.549 --> 01:11:35.217
- Are you okay?
- It's okay. I'm okay.

01:11:35.467 --> 01:11:37.636
God. I was so afraid.

01:11:37.886 --> 01:11:40.222
I thought I wasn't ever
gonna see you again.

01:11:40.431 --> 01:11:42.182
Me too.

01:11:42.433 --> 01:11:43.935
We've got things to talk about.

01:11:44.476 --> 01:11:46.644
I only want to talk about
what you want to tell me.

01:11:46.895 --> 01:11:50.983
I want to tell you everything.
Everything.

01:11:52.150 --> 01:11:54.404
Get that gurney over here.
Get over here.

01:11:54.611 --> 01:11:56.528
We lost him.

01:11:58.822 --> 01:12:00.325
- I want to stand up.
- I got him.

01:12:00.574 --> 01:12:02.576
- Sure you can hold on?
- I gotta see him.

01:12:02.784 --> 01:12:04.870
- You don't want to see this.
- Yes, I do.

01:12:05.078 --> 01:12:06.663
- Take it easy.
- Yes, I do.

01:12:06.914 --> 01:12:10.126
- Allow me. Allow me.
- Go ahead.

01:12:15.881 --> 01:12:18.299
You recognize him?

01:12:18.508 --> 01:12:21.469
Yeah. He was down here trying
to deliver me a pizza...

01:12:21.718 --> 01:12:23.804
...10 minutes before I got the call.

01:12:24.013 --> 01:12:26.432
I told him to fuck off.

01:12:26.642 --> 01:12:28.225
That's enough these days.

01:12:33.605 --> 01:12:35.775
Just give it a minute.

01:12:35.983 --> 01:12:38.153
We'll be driving,
and you'll be flying.

01:12:38.361 --> 01:12:40.613
Whatever you say.

01:12:43.906 --> 01:12:46.619
What a piece of shit.

01:13:15.603 --> 01:13:17.689
Nice shoes.

01:13:22.193 --> 01:13:24.111
Italian.

01:13:26.322 --> 01:13:29.116
You hung up, Stu.

01:13:29.325 --> 01:13:31.952
I didn't get a chance to say goodbye.

01:13:33.705 --> 01:13:36.497
I feel bad about the pizza guy.

01:13:37.082 --> 01:13:40.378
But I couldn't miss seeing
you and Kelly reunited.

01:13:40.629 --> 01:13:43.506
You don't have to thank me.
Nobody ever does.

01:13:43.756 --> 01:13:47.383
I just hope
your newfound honesty lasts.

01:13:47.592 --> 01:13:52.181
Because it if doesn't,
you'll be hearing from me.

01:14:20.790 --> 01:14:22.792
<i>Isn't it funny?</i>

01:14:23.043 --> 01:14:27.462
<i>You hear a phone ring,
and it could be anybody.</i>

01:14:28.173 --> 01:14:32.592
<i>But a ringing phone
has to be answered, doesn't it?</i>

01:14:34.678 --> 01:14:37.139
<i>Doesn't it?</i>

01:15:01.120 --> 01:15:02.079
Hello?

